Had the sweet experience of joining Isabella for her St. Augustine field trip.

We had the honor of meeting Gypsi, Summer, Tursi, and their pod at the Dolphin Research Center. It was such an incredible experience to learn about these beautiful and brilliant mammals, see them so well cared for, and to play with them. 

The Dolphin research Center cares for mammals deemed unreleasable back into the wild, provides them with proper medical care, and studies their behaviors and needs in order to provide information to better serve them. It was refreshing to see the dolphins so well respected. If they didn’t want to play, they didn’t have to and we’re still given ample fish and affection. Lucky for us, we had dolphins that wanted to play, A LOT, and even some that snuck over from another area to play with us and her pals. 

If you want to support a non-profit and learn more about marine life, I cannot recommend a drive down to Marathon, FL enough. Your participation helps to fund their care.
Our Spring Break adventures seem to be centered around marine life this year. This was by far our favorite part so far.

Feeling a little sentimental today as someone told me Parker was made for our family and I’ve looked back at everything we’ve been through to get him here. 

Looking back at the moments just before my life changed forever. “The calm before the storm.” 

I had just sat on a beach during this vacation we had talked about having for 11 YEARS, and told Seth that life was TOO GOOD and that I was waiting for the hard to come. I didn’t realize that it would come so soon. Literally days later.

But in having to process my situation with as little pain as possible, I overlooked this amazingly dreamy experience I had with Seth and the girls.

So although literally one hour after this photo, I miscarried baby #3 and was launched into months of constant cancer treatments, this moment was good and I’m putting it here because it doesn’t deserve to be buried under pain. 

Would I change the experience I had? Yes, I absolutely would, 10 out of 10 would not recommend. But I’ve chosen to grow from it. I’ve chosen to heal. I’ve chosen to remember this moment with my girls in the middle of a little beach in Maui where we swam with wild turtles.

A little love sweetens even the smallest moments.
